One of the protesters says he wants the church to stop perpetuating homophobia which extends to hate crimes in the townships. JOHANNESBURG Members of the LGBTI community are picketing outside the Grace Bible Church in defence of gay rights after a guest pastor said homosexuality was unnatural during a recent sermon.Many have taken to social media using the hashtag occupy grace bible church while demonstrators gather outside the Soweto church.One of the protesters, Cameron Modisane, says they want the church to stop perpetuating homophobia which also extends to hate crimes in the townships. Modisane says the gay community is tired of being compared to sinners and adulterers. You can t walk by as a gay man or a lesbian in the township without someone passing swear words at you or being raped or killed. We are scared for our lives and it all starts in the church. 